RCE HR Core upgrade - Files are in error status post Upgrade<p>We need to resolve this issue as we have planned payroll activity.</p>Product Area selected: SAP ERP HCM, localization for CEE<br />Component selected (Manual Selection): PA-AS<br /><br />--- Steps to Reproduce ---<br />NOTE TO SAP SUPPORT: I give my approval for SAP Support to reproduce the issue described, while connected to my impacted non-production environments, using any steps provided in the description below or provided later, even if the steps result in a change being made, until the issue is closed.<br /><br />--- Description ---<br />Dear Team,<br />Post HR Core upgrade, Files are getting stuck in SM58. the below are the error:<br /><br />RFC_BI_X7H   RSAR_TRFC_DATA_RECEIVED        P7HCLNT010                       19.12.2022 09:13:25 A newer version of data type /BIC/B<br /> <br />RFC_BI_X7H   RSAR_TRFC_DATA_RECEIVED        P7HCLNT010                       19.12.2022 09:13:11 A newer version of data type /BIC/B<br /> <br />RFC_BI_X7H   RSAR_TRFC_DATA_RECEIVED        P7HCLNT010                       19.12.2022 10:12:08 ERROR REQU_DK8IFGPC4FESCZ8FWD98DC6P<br /> <br />We have tried to execute LUW but after some time new files are gets into error.<br /><br />Could you please check this issue.12.28.2022 08:15:53 work_notes\nOliver Ziegele (D031922) has requested to escalate this Case. ESC0360551 created.\n12.27.2022 11:45:51 u_customer_comments\nDear Alberto, The files were getting stuck in SM58 and now we are getting the error message no. SY359. Could you please help on this.\n12.27.2022 11:45:50 work_notes\ncould you please help on this issue - 958385 / 2022 The files are getting stuck in SM58 at P32 end after upgrade\r\nThe files were getting stuck in SM58 and now we are getting the error message no, SY359\r\nsee screenshot in email attached\r\n&nbsp;\n12.27.2022 11:44:09 comments\nRetrieve\n12.27.2022 09:33:19 work_notes\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #1f497d;\">The files were getting stuck in SM58 and now we are getting the below error message. Could you please help on this.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #1f497d;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #1f497d;\"><img src=\"blob:https://fiorilaunchpad.sap.com/sap/fiori/mcsqdassistant/snow/c98655f2-9e13-4101-b2b5-50b8f70fdb53\" width=\"842\" height=\"263\" /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #1f497d;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #1f3864;\">Thanks &amp; Regards,</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #1f3864;\">Steven Thyagu</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #1f3864;\">Infosys Ltd.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #1f3864;\">RCE Project Manager</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #1f3864;\">Providing Services to Novartis AMS ERP</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #1f3864;\">ERP Operations</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #1f3864;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #1f3864;\">M +91 82960 48115</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #1f3864;\">Bangalore, India.</span></p>\n12.22.2022 02:50:55 comments\nDear Steven,&nbsp;\nAfter analyzing the issue on SM58 I'd like to recommend the following KBA:&nbsp;\n<a href=\"https://launchpad.support.sap.com/#/notes/2684422\">2684422 - \"ERROR REQU_xxx PG# nnn In BW\" in the transaction SM58</a>\nIf you have any question please let me know.&nbsp;\nKind regards,<br />Alberto&nbsp;\n&nbsp;\n12.22.2022 02:23:05 comments\nDear Steven,\r\nNow that I have access to the system, I will reproduce the issue on the system and provide you more feedback on the next steps for the resolution of the root issue.&nbsp;\r\nI'll get back to you within the hour.&nbsp;\r\nKind regards,<br />Alberto&nbsp;\n12.22.2022 02:08:20 work_notes\n has declined escalation ESC0357475.\n12.22.2022 02:08:18 work_notes\nEscalation ESC0357475 has updated:\n22/12/2022 14:08:18 - Karl Hearty (I008787) (Internal Info)\nDe-Escalation justification:  ### automatic processing by MCC Q&D Team  ###\r\nDe-escalation justification: ### automatic processing by MCC Q&D Team ###\r\nJudgement: Not Relevant for MCC\r\nIssue/Impact: Priority has been lowered.\r\nNext Action: Standard support process continues. For information on Technical Backoffice Engagement escalations please see KBA 3205358. https://launchpad.support.sap.com/#/notes/3205358\r\n \n\n\n12.22.2022 02:00:56 work_notes\nOliver Ziegele (D031922) has requested to escalate this Case. ESC0357475 created.\n12.22.2022 01:35:03 comments\n​Connection Type: &nbsp;&nbsp;R/3 Support with SNC/SSO<br />Customer system:&nbsp; P32\nDear Customer,\nthe service connection to your system &nbsp;is working fine now, I moved your case to the last processor at SAP.\nBest regards,<br />G&uuml;nther Schmitt<br />External<br />On behalf of SAP Product Support<br />Remote Connection Support Centre EMEA\n12.22.2022 01:35:02 work_notes\n​Connection Type: &nbsp;&nbsp;R/3 Support with SNC/SSO<br />Customer system:&nbsp; P32\nThe &nbsp;R/3 Support with SNC/SSO service connection to the customer system P32 is working fine\nYou have to use SAPGui version <strong>greater</strong> 760 with patch level 7 on your PC: &nbsp;<a href=\"https://jam4.sapjam.com/blogs/show/MZi4CCJcYv1MmHlKkesOzB\">https://jam4.sapjam.com/blogs/show/MZi4CCJcYv1MmHlKkesOzB</a>\nPlease check the settings of your SAP Secure Logon Client on your local computer:\nSAP Secure Logon Client -&gt; File -&gt; Options -&gt; Select \"Legacy Compatibility Mode\" and \"Allow Manual Server Trust\" -&gt; save\nBest regards,<br />G&uuml;nther\n12.22.2022 01:24:34 comments\nDear Steven,\nThank you for the update, I've lowered the priority and will continue my work on the solution, the first step was to connect to the system but I would like inform you, that I got a SAP router error, when I tried to connect to your system, therefore I forward this incident to our network team, who will help for you.\nMy colleagues will contact you as soon as possible and send the case back to me afterwards.\nBest regards,<br />Alberto,<br />SAP Product Support\n12.22.2022 01:24:34 work_notes\nHello Colleagues,&nbsp;\nWhen I try connect&nbsp; the system, I get an error message:\n---------------------------<br />SAP GUI for Windows 770<br />---------------------------<br />SAP system message:<br />&nbsp;Unencrypted communication is rejected by this system<br />---------------------------<br />OK &nbsp;&nbsp;<br />---------------------------\nSystem id, number: P32\nPlease help to the customer. When the connection is working, please put back this incident to my name.\nThank you in advance.\n12.22.2022 10:06:10 u_customer_comments\nDear Alberto,<br />Please change the priority to High. We are awaiting response from SAP from last 2- 3 days. Please treat this on priority and update us asap.<br />This issue is occurring post-production upgrade.\n12.22.2022 09:26:37 comments\nDear Steven,\nMy name is&nbsp;&nbsp;Alberto from SAP Product Support Team, and I am going to work with you.\nFirstly, I must draw your attention to the priority chosen for this case, the priority \"Very High\" is usually reserved for situations where your productive system is down and this is resulting in a serious loss for your company. If this is not the case then kindly lower the priority of the message to \"High\".\nPlease refer to note <a href=\"https://launchpad.support.sap.com/#/notes/67739\">67739</a>, for further details.\nIn case you believe the priority should be kept as Very High, please answer the following questions regarding the business impact:\n1. Is the Productive System is completely down? (Yes/No)\n1.1 &nbsp;What is the Production System ID?\n2. Is there an Imminent go-live or upgrade is jeopardized? (Yes/No)\n2.1 What is the Planned Go Live Date:\n3. Are the Core Business Processes are seriously affected (Yes/No)\n3.1 What is the Core Business process?\n3.2 How does this impact the process?\n4. Is there a workaround available? (Yes/No)\n4.1 if yes, what is the workaround used?\n5. What is the estimated financial loss within 24hrs?\n6. Number of Users affected:\n7. For Business Impact Description:\n- What is the problem?\n- How does this issue impact the business?\nPlease answer the question thoroughly for a better assessment of the issue.&nbsp;\nFrom there, I will be able to better understand the issue and start the analysis on how to properly provide a solution.\nIf you judge that any other information may be useful, please attach to the case.\nI will be waiting on your feedback. &nbsp;&nbsp;\nBest regards,<br />Alberto,<br />SAP Product Support\n12.22.2022 08:39:36 work_notes\nEscalation ESC0357145 has updated:\n22.12.2022 11:39:35 - Alexandr Vornichesko (I071680) (Internal Info)\nDe-Escalation justification:  ### Q&D Team Qualification 2022-12-22 08:39:31 UTC ###\nJudgement: Not Relevant to MCC\nIssue/Impact: This has been a P2 ticket. Customer has raised to P1 without an indication why business impact became more severe (no critical due date, or back log has increased).\nNext Action: Standard support process continues. For information on Technical Backoffice Engagement escalations please see KBA 3205358. https://launchpad.support.sap.com/#/notes/3205358 \n\n\n12.22.2022 08:39:35 work_notes\n has declined escalation ESC0357145.\n12.22.2022 08:27:49 work_notes\nOliver Ziegele (D031922) has requested to escalate this Case. ESC0357145 created.\n12.20.2022 10:08:33 comments\nHi,\nI am forwarding your case to BC-BW, they will assist you soon.\nRegards,\nMeera\n12.20.2022 10:08:33 work_notes\nHi Colleagues,\nCustomer is getting error as RSAR_TRFC_DATA_RECEIVED in LUW in SM58. Kindly assist.\nRegards,\nMeera\n12.20.2022 09:31:55 comments\nDear Customer,\nThanks for the information provided so far.\nThe expert colleagues in this area will contact you with updates.\nWe highly appreciate your patience.\nMany Thanks &amp; Regards,\nSzilvia\nQueue Manager\n
